  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "E&I Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job scope:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Dealing with management, planning &amp; execution of engineering &amp; maintenance jobs in plant</li>\n  <li>Managing a team to provide Electrical &amp; Instrumentation maintenance</li>\n  <li>Evaluate all maintenance planning and work execution documents (e.g., Long Term Maintenance Plan, Critical Equipment List, etc.).</li>\n  <li>Draft and revise new/current maintenance work procedures and work instructions.</li>\n  <li>Collaborating with senior/superintendent to analyze data of plants’ critical equipment from predictive to preventive maintenance activities to make recommendations and/or countermeasures, to upkeep proper documentation of maintenance and improvement works, to fulfill ISO requirements by establishing procedures and calibration forms, and training of personnel.</li>\n  <li>Supporting the Senior/Superintendent to plan, execute, and coordinate the Shut Down Maintenance (SDM) work in assigned plants, including statutory inspection of equipment.</li>\n  <li>Provide prompt and effective technical support to assigned plants, including the production, technical, and coordination sections, as well as to external vendors.</li>\n  <li>Lead and conduct troubleshooting of complex problems to work with relevant stakeholders to resolve systematically and identify effective countermeasures.</li>\n  <li>Propose improvement ideas and lead team initiatives for management consideration as well to drive the implementation of improvement initiatives and projects.</li>\n  <li>Execute assigned engineering and minor modification works, focusing on electrical &amp; instrumentation aspects, in assigned plants.</li>\n  <li>Conduct training for internal stakeholders and in-house contractors on specific technical topics for presentations and toolbox briefings.</li>\n  <li>Bachelor degree in any electrical engineering or related courses</li>\n  <li>Electrical &amp; Instrumentation experience in pharmaceutical &amp; petrochemical engineering industries</li>\n</ul>",
